            "answer_text": "I do agree with sonali raghunath's suggestions. She is well explained each and every reaction properly. Na2CO3 (sodium carbonate) + H2O => Na2O + H2CO3 (carbonic acid) => H2O +CO2 + 2NaOH Keep in mind that this reaction does not go all the way to completion, but that it is still a fairly strong base. The reaction of sodium bicarbonate (baking soda) is similar, but goes to completion even less, making it a weaker base. ",
